{"schema_version": 2, "ts": "2026-05-11T00:00:00Z", "event": "clarify_critic", "feature": "promote-lifecycle-state-out-of-eventslog-full-reads", "parent_epic_loaded": true, "findings": [{"text": "The assessment rates Intent Clarity as HIGH, claiming the goal is unambiguous structural promotion, but the ticket's Research hooks list a thin-reader-wrapper option that would not promote storage at all — the mechanism class is research-deferred, not settled.", "origin": "primary"}, {"text": "The HIGH Intent Clarity rating is internally contradictory: Why-it-matters rules out wrappers ('caches the wrong-layer choice without fixing it'); Research hooks re-admits them as a legitimate candidate to evaluate.", "origin": "primary"}, {"text": "The HIGH Scope Boundedness rating cites a four-field in-scope list (criticality, tier, tasks_total, rework_cycles), but the Problem section names five fields including tasks_checked and Research hooks asks whether phase/complexity_override/criticality_override-reasons should be in too.", "origin": "primary"}, {"text": "Several constraints cited as 'dense and specific' are hedged ('phase should probably stay derived... Confirm during research'; 'gone (or justified by a clear reason to keep)') — research-pending boundaries dressed up as constraints.", "origin": "primary"}, {"text": "Research hooks state 'Sequencing requires #189 to settle the events.log emission shape first', but blocked-by:[] in frontmatter — either the ticket is genuinely blocked-by #189 or the sequencing language is overstated, and the assessment did not flag this.", "origin": "primary"}, {"text": "Requirements Alignment HIGH asserts 'no conflicts detected' without verifying that atomic tempfile + os.replace composes safely with concurrent overnight runs doing RMW updates (e.g., incrementing rework_cycles) under the 'without locking' constraint.", "origin": "primary"}, {"text": "Requirements Alignment HIGH was declared on a narrow sweep (only project.md:27 and pipeline.md