 radius, and explicit design judgment calls.", "Sequencing/parent-dep: noted that #189 has landed (status:complete in backlog frontmatter, confirmed by commit 6ab3760-area) so the sequencing prerequisite is satisfied; the blocked-by:[] field is now consistent with reality and need not be amended.", "Added research consideration: design must address RMW-safety under the 'no locks' constraint — atomic-replace alone does not prevent lost updates from concurrent overnight runs writing the same lifecycle's RMW fields. Research must surface the chosen coordination primitive (single-writer-per-key, field-partitioning by writer-role, CAS, or another).", "Added research consideration: verify the actual post-#189 events.log emission shape (read the landed code, not just the spec) so this design targets the stable baseline rather than a stale assumption.", "Added research consideration: locate the alternative-exploration's specific state-storage recommendations in research/lifecycle-discovery-token-audit/research.md and treat them as evaluated-inputs in the research phase — neither reflexively adopted nor reflexively dismissed."], "dismissals": [{"finding_index": 3, "rationale": "The hedges flagged ('phase should probably stay derived... Confirm during research'; 'gone (or justified by a clear reason to keep)') are bounded research-deferred decisions — exclude-unless-research-justifies — not open scope. The candidate set of fields and the exclusion-default for phase are both closed. Standard research-phase ticket shape."}, {"finding_index": 6, "rationale": "The RMW-safety concern is a real research consideration (added to applied_fixes above) but does not constitute a requirements-alignment failure. The ticket's Constraints section explicitly names multi-writer safety and the 'without locking' constraint; requirements alignment is preserved because the design space is bounded by those constraints and the existing atomic-write pattern. Whether the chosen mechanism actually satisfies the constraint is research-phase work, not a clarify-phase alignment failure."}, {"finding_index": 7, "rationale": "Per project.md:67-72 conditional-loading rules, lifecycle-state work maps to project.md general constraints + pipeline.md state-file precedents; observability/multi-agent/remote-access are not in the relevant conditional-load set for this feature. The sweep was scoped per the documented loading protocol, not narrow by oversight."}], "status": "ok"}
